        720
      ],
      "id": "131fd9a6-49f1-451c-9d6c-87ef1bcd4979",
      "name": "AI Agent"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🕘 STEP 1 — Auto Start Every Morning\n\n**What it does:**\nThis node is the \"alarm clock\" of the whole workflow.\nIt automatically starts the workflow every day at **9:00 AM**.\n\nYou don't need to click anything — it runs by itself every morning.\n\n**No changes needed here.** Just make sure n8n is running on your server.",
        "height": 332,
        "width": 300,
        "color": 5
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -16,
        928
      ],
      "id": "99b2e440-2fc8-4c9c-a252-4bf75469dd65",
      "name": "Note: Schedule Trigger"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⚠️ CRITICAL ALERT — READ BEFORE USING!\n\n**Groq Free Tier Daily Limits (llama-3.3-70b-versatile):**\n- 🔴 **~14,400 tokens per minute**\n- 🔴 **~1,000 requests per day** (approximately)\n- Each cover letter uses ~800–1,200 tokens\n\n**This means you can safely generate only about 10–20 cover letters per day on the free plan.**\n\n---\n\n### 🛑 HOW TO LIMIT YOUR LINKEDIN URL\nBefore running, go to the **\"Set Search Parameters\"** node and make your LinkedIn URL as specific as possible.\n\n**Tips to filter results:**\n- Add specific keywords: `keywords=Marketing+Manager`\n- Use `f_E=` for experience level (1=Internship, 2=Entry, 3=Associate, 4=Mid-Senior, 5=Director)\n- Use `f_JT=` for job type (F=Full-time, P=Part-time, C=Contract)\n- Use `f_TPR=r86400` (already set — shows only last 24 hours posts ✅)\n\n**Example of a well-filtered URL:**\n`...keywords=Marketing&f_E=2&f_JT=F&f_TPR=r86400`\n\nIf your search returns **more than 20 jobs**, Groq WILL hit the rate limit and the workflow will fail midway! 🚨",
        "height": 692,
        "width": 480,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        0,
        0
      ],
      "id": "a3afabd3-f498-4ae0-ae0b-29ffabb6ef4e",
      "name": "Note: ⚠️ GROQ RATE LIMIT ALERT"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔗 STEP 2 — Set Your LinkedIn Search Link\n\n**What it does:**\nThis is where you paste the LinkedIn Jobs search URL.\nThe URL tells the scraper *which jobs* to look for.\n\n**Current settings:**\n- 📍 Location: Kathmandu\n- 🕐 Time filter: Last 24 hours only\n\n**How to customize:**\n1. Go to LinkedIn Jobs in your browser\n2. Search with your desired filters (location, job type, keywords)\n3. Copy the URL from the browser address bar\n4. Paste it here as the value of `Linkedin_url`\n\n⚠️ **Keep the search narrow** — the more specific your URL, the fewer results, and the less likely you are to hit the Groq AI rate limit!",
        "height": 504,
        "width": 564,
        "color": 5
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        496,
        128
      ],
      "id": "08209662-420d-492a-95b0-d41ed7023c74",
      "name": "Note: Set Search Parameters"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 STEP 3 — Scrape LinkedIn Job Listings\n\n**What it does:**\nThis node visits your LinkedIn URL and automatically collects all the job listings it finds — like a robot reading the page for you.\n\nIt collects details like:\n- Job title\n- Company name\n- Job description\n- Company LinkedIn URL\n- Location, posted date\n\n**Tool used:** Apify (a web scraping service)\n\n**You need:** An Apify account and API key connected in the credentials.\n\n⏱️ This step may take 1–3 minutes to complete.",
        "height": 504,
        "width": 340,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1088,
        128
      ],
      "id": "49b1bf6b-1627-43ee-8ed9-f2ac1be969ea",
      "name": "Note: Apify Scraper"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 📋 STEP 4 — Load Already-Saved Jobs from Sheet\n\n**What it does:**\nThis node reads your Google Sheet to get the list of jobs that were **already saved before**.\n\nThis is used in the next step to avoid creating duplicate cover letters for the same job.\n\n**Make sure:**\n- Your Google Sheet is connected properly\n- The sheet has a column called `link` (job URL)\n\nThis runs at the same time as Step 3.",
        "height": 448,
        "width": 324,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1472,
        176
      ],
      "id": "c9fd1186-f84f-4d99-89ba-0fc5f38902f5",
      "name": "Note: Fetch Existing Leads"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔍 STEP 5 — Remove Duplicate Jobs\n\n**What it does:**\nCompares the newly scraped jobs (Step 3) with what's already in the sheet (Step 4).\n\nIf a job was already saved before, it is **removed from the list** so we don't write a duplicate cover letter.\n\nOnly **brand new jobs** pass through to the next step.\n\n**How it matches:** It compares the job `link` (URL). If the link already exists in the sheet, that job is skipped.",
        "height": 400,
        "width": 320,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1840,
        224
      ],
      "id": "86dbda4e-61d9-49fc-b54f-36e75b744b3c",
      "name": "Note: Deduplicate"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔄 STEP 6 — Process Jobs One by One\n\n**What it does:**\nInstead of processing all jobs at once (which would crash Groq), this node sends them **one at a time** through the rest of the workflow.\n\nAfter each job is fully processed and saved, it comes back here to pick up the next one.\n\nThink of it like a conveyor belt — one item at a time.\n\n**The loop ends** when all new jobs have been processed.",
        "height": 396,
        "width": 316,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        2192,
        224
      ],
      "id": "bcc8dd28-753c-446e-849a-d8937ca7bf25",
      "name": "Note: Loop Over Items"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⏳ STEP 7 — Wait 10 Seconds Between Jobs\n\n**What it does:**\nAdds a **10-second pause** between each job being processed.\n\n**Why?** To avoid sending too many requests to Groq AI too fast.\nGroq has a limit of how many requests it can handle per minute.\nThis pause keeps things slow and steady so the AI doesn't get overloaded.\n\n💡 If you're still hitting rate limit errors, increase this wait time to 30 or 60 seconds.",
        "height": 380,
        "width": 300,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        304,
        1024
      ],
      "id": "518c6a6b-0c9f-4605-beec-9a0f8e3e2c27",
      "name": "Note: Wait"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ✍️ STEP 8 — Write a Cover Letter Using AI\n\n**What it does:**\nThis is the main AI step. It takes the job details (title, company, description) and asks the AI to **write a professional cover letter** tailored to that specific job.\n\nThe cover letter is:\n- 300–400 words\n- Formatted as a proper business letter\n- Personalized to the job and company\n\n**AI Model used:** Groq → llama-3.3-70b-versatile (connected below)\n\n⚠️ **Reminder:** Each cover letter = ~800–1,200 tokens. Keep your daily volume to 10–20 jobs maximum on the free Groq plan.",
        "height": 456,
        "width": 360,
        "color": 2
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        624,
        1040
      ],
      "id": "83d439f8-ddeb-4303-b04c-72679c4133af",
      "name": "Note: AI Agent"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🧠 AI Brain — Groq Language Model\n\n**What it does:**\nThis is the actual AI engine that powers the cover letter writing above.\n\n**Model:** llama-3.3-70b-versatile (fast & free on Groq)\n\n**You need:** A free Groq account at groq.com and your API key added in n8n credentials.\n\n**Free Tier Limits:**\n- ~14,400 tokens/minute\n- ~1,000 requests/day\n- Roughly **10–20 cover letters per day** safely\n\nThis node is connected to the AI Agent above.",
        "height": 448,
        "width": 340,
        "color": 2
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1712,
        960
      ],
      "id": "097aac80-bda4-4381-a54b-0306c8cbed5f",
      "name": "Note: Groq Model"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🗂️ STEP 9 — Organize the Data\n\n**What it does:**\nTakes all the information collected so far (job title, company, cover letter, date, etc.) and **neatly organizes it** into labeled fields, ready to be written into the Google Sheet.\n\nThink of this as putting everything into the right columns before saving.",
        "height": 308,
        "width": 300,
        "color": 5
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1008,
        960
      ],
      "id": "e2783624-0c92-4e1e-92d0-e22df5f79de9",
      "name": "Note: Edit Fields"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 💾 STEP 10 — Save to Google Sheet\n\n**What it does:**\nAdds a new row to your Google Sheet with all the job info and the generated cover letter.\n\nEach row contains:\n- Date scraped\n- Job title & company name\n- Job link\n- Company LinkedIn URL\n- Location & posted date\n- ✅ The AI-generated cover letter\n\nAfter saving, the workflow loops back to process the next new job.",
        "height": 432,
        "width": 320,
        "color": 5
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1344,
        960
      ],
      "id": "b9d4c9a6-1a5d-409c-9c7b-9c9c4ef2dafe",
      "name": "Note: Append to Sheet"
    }
  ],
